#. id="Bu-Pc.21">
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 21: the training rule on the instruction"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.21.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.263"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="484"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time the senior monks who instructed the nuns were receiving robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines."

msgstr "When the monks from the group of six found out about this, they thought, “Well then, let’s instruct the nuns.”"

msgstr "They then went to the nuns and said, “Come to us, Sisters, and we too will instruct you.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="485"></a>Soon afterwards those nuns went to the monks from the group of six, bowed down to them, and sat down to one side."

msgstr "But after giving just a short teaching, those monks spent the day on pointless talk."

msgstr "They then dismissed the nuns, saying, “Go, Sisters.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Those nuns then went to the Master, bowed down to him, and stood to one side."

msgstr "And the Master said to them, “Nuns, I hope the instruction was effective?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, how could the instruction be effective?"

msgstr "After giving just a short teaching, the monks from the group of six spent the day on pointless talk, and then dismissed us.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The Master instructed, inspired, and gladdened those nuns with a teaching."

msgstr "The nuns  <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.264"></a> bowed down to the Master, circumambulated him with their right side towards him, and departed."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="486"></a>The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned the monks from the group of six, “Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them …"

msgstr "“Foolish men, how can you give just a short teaching to the nuns, and then spend the day on pointless talk, before dismissing them?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”"

msgstr "…"

msgstr "and after rebuking them …"

msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><p></p><span class="kamma"><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="487"></a>‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, it should appoint monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns."

msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="488"></a>Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgstr "The Order appoints monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns."

msgstr "Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns should remain silent."

msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="489"></a>A second time I speak on this matter …"

msgstr "A third time I speak on this matter:"

msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgstr "The Order appoints monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns."

msgstr "Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns should remain silent."

msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="490"></a>The Order has appointed monks so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns."

msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></span><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="491"></a>Then, after criticizing the monks from the group of six in many ways for being difficult to support …"

msgstr "the Master said, “And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="492"></a>‘If a monk who has not been agreed upon instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgstr " <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.265"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="493"></a>In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.21.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="494"></a>After being appointed to do so, the senior monks who instructed the nuns still received robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines."

msgstr "When they found out about this, the monks from the group of six said, “Well then, let’s go outside the boundary, appoint each other as instructors of the nuns, and then instruct them.”"

msgstr "After doing just that, they again went to the nuns and said, “Sisters, we too have been appointed."

msgstr "Come to us, and we too will instruct you.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="495"></a>Once again the nuns went to the monks from the group of six and everything unfolded as before. <a class="wt-pa" id="496"></a>"

msgstr "The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned the monks from the group of six, “Is it true, monks, that you are acting like this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them …"

msgstr "“Foolish men, how can you give just a short teaching to the nuns, and then spend the day on pointless talk, before dismissing them?”"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”"

msgstr "…"

msgstr "and after rebuking them …"

msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><span class="rule"><p>
msgstr "“Monks, you should appoint a monk who possesses eight qualities as an instructor of the nuns:"

#. </p><span class="sutta"><ul><li><span
#. class="note"><fn><span class="ref"></span></span></li><li><a class="pts-vp-en"
#. id="BD.2.266"></a></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></span><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.267"></a>Monks, you should appoint a monk who possesses these eight qualities as an instructor of the nuns.”"

#. </p></span><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.21.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="497"></a><term>A</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>…"

msgstr "The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</gloss>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="498"></a><term>Who has not been agreed upon</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>who has not been agreed upon through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.</gloss>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="499"></a><term>Nuns</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>they have been given the full ordination by both Orders.</gloss>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="500"></a><term>Instructs</term>:"

#. </p><gloss><p>
msgstr "If he instructs in the eight rules to be respected, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he instructs in any other teaching, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="501"></a>The monk who has been agreed upon should sweep the precincts, set out water for drinking and for washing the feet, prepare a seat, get hold of a companion, and then sit down."

msgstr "The nuns should go there, bow down to the monk, and sit down to one side."

msgstr "The monk should then ask them, “Sisters, are you all present?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If they say, “We’re all present, Venerable,” he should say, “Are you keeping the eight rules to be respected?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If they say, “We are,” he should present the instruction,<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Niyyādetabbo</i>. For the meaning of this word in this context, see the usage in the origin story to the next rule, <span class="ref">MS.2.517</span>, and the explanation at <span class="ref">Sp.4.792.10</span>, <span class="ref">Sp.4.800.25</span>.</span>"

msgstr "“This is the instruction.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If they  <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.268"></a> say, “We’re not,” he should recite the rules to be respected:"

#. </p><ul><li></li><li><span class="note" hidden><i lang="pi"></i><i
#. lang="pi"></i></span></li><li></li><li><a class="pts-vp-en"
#. id="BD.2.269"></a></li><li><span class="note" hidden><i lang="pi"></i><i
#. lang="pi"></i></span></li><li></li><li></li><li><span
#. class="note"><fn><i lang="pi"></i></span></li></ul><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="502"></a>If they say, “We’re all present, Venerable,” and he instructs them with another teaching, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.<span class="note">*<fn>This seems to say that if the nuns are all present then the monk must always give an <i lang="pi">ovāda</i> that consists in teaching the eight <i lang="pi">garudhammas</i>.This, however, needs to be seen in light of the further subdivision given in the text above, where the instruction in the <i lang="pi">garudhammas</i> is to be given only when the nuns say they are not practicing them.If the nuns are practicing the <i lang="pi">garudhammas</i>, there seems to be no restriction on the nature of the <i lang="pi">ovāda</i>.</span>"

msgstr "If they say, “We’re not all present, Venerable,” and he instructs them in the eight rules to be respected, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he does not present the instruction, but he gives them another teaching,<span class="note">*<fn>According to the commentary (<span class="ref">Sp.4.800.25</span>) this simply means not having said, “Sisters, this is the instruction,” <i lang="pi">ovādaṃ aniyyādetvāti eso bhaginiyo ovādoti avatvā</i>. This, however, does seem contrived. A more natural meaning might be to see this statement in conjunction with the previous one, and the two together might then be paraphrased as follows: If the nuns say they are not all present, then one should not instruct in the eight rules to be respected, nor in any other teaching. In any case, once “Sisters, this is the instruction” has been said, it seems any teaching can be given; see origin story to the next rule, <span class="ref">MS.2.517</span>.</span>"

msgstr "then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p></gloss><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.21.3.2"></a> <a class="wt-pa" id="503"></a>If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.270"></a> the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="504"></a>If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="505"></a>If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="506"></a>If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete and he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="507"></a>If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is complete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is complete and he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="508"></a>If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete and he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.271"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="509"></a>If it is a legitimate procedure but he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="510"></a>If it is a legitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="511"></a>If it is a legitimate procedure and he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure and he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure and he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><hr><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="512"></a>If it is a legitimate procedure but he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he perceives it as illegitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete and he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="513"></a>If it is a legitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is complete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order of nuns is complete and he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="514"></a>If it is a legitimate procedure and he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure and he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure and he perceives it as legitimate, and the Order of nuns is complete and he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.21.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="515"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he gives a summary;"

msgstr "if he questions them;"

msgstr "if he recites when asked to do so;"

msgstr " <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.272"></a> if he asks a question;"

msgstr "if he replies when asked a question;"

msgstr "if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;"

msgstr "if it is to a trainee nun;"

msgstr "if it is to a novice nun;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="516"></a>The first rule, the training rule on the instruction, is finished."

#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 22: the training rule on gone down"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.22.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.273"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="517"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time the senior monks were instructing the nuns in turn, and on one occasion it was the turn of Venerable Cūḷapanthaka."

msgstr "The nuns said, “Today the instruction won’t be effective, since Venerable Cūḷapanthaka will just be repeating the same utterance over and over.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Soon afterwards those nuns went to Cūḷapanthaka, bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgstr "Cūḷapanthaka then said to them, “Are you all present, Sisters?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“We’re all present, Venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Are you keeping the eight rules to be respected?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“We are.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "After saying, “This is the instruction,” he spoke the same utterance again and again:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="518"></a>“For the heedful one possessed of the higher mind,"

#. <br>
msgstr "For the sage training on the path to sagacity,"

#. <br>
msgstr "There are no sorrows for such a one,"

#. <br>
msgstr "The peaceful one, who is always mindful.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.274"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="519"></a>And the nuns said, “Didn’t we say that the instruction wouldn’t be effective, that Venerable Cūḷapanthaka would just be repeating the same utterance over and over?”"

msgstr "But Cūḷapanthaka overheard that conversation between the nuns."

msgstr "He then rose up into the air, walked back and forth in space, and he stood, sat down, and lay down there."

msgstr "He emitted smoke and fire, and he disappeared, all the while speaking the same utterance and many other sayings by the Buddha."

msgstr "And the nuns said, “It’s astonishing and amazing!"

msgstr "No previous instruction has been as effective as this one from Venerable Cūḷapanthaka!”"

msgstr "And Cūḷapanthaka kept on instructing those nuns until the dark of night, and then dismissed them, saying, “Go, Sisters.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="520"></a>But because the gates to the town were closed, those nuns stayed the night outside and entered in the morning."

msgstr "People complained and criticized them, “These nuns aren’t celibate."

msgstr "They spend the night in the monastery with the monks and only now do they enter the town.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="521"></a>The monks heard the complaints of those people, and the monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized Cūḷapanthaka, “How can Venerable Cūḷapanthaka instruct the nuns after the sun has set?”"

msgstr "…"

msgstr "“Is it true, Cūḷapanthaka, that you did this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "Cūḷapanthaka, how can you instruct the nuns after the sun has set?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without  <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.275"></a> it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="522"></a>‘Even if he has been agreed upon, if a monk instructs the nuns after sunset, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.21.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="523"></a><term>Who has been agreed upon</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>who has been agreed upon through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.</gloss>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="524"></a><term>After sunset</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>after the sun has gone down.</gloss>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="525"></a><term>The nuns</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>they have been given the full ordination by both Orders.</gloss>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="526"></a><term>Instructs</term>:"

msgstr "<gloss>if he instructs in the eight rules to be respected or he gives any other teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.</gloss>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.22.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="527"></a>If the sun has set, and he perceives that it has, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If the sun has set, but he is unsure if it has, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If the sun has set, but he perceives that it has not, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="528"></a>If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If the sun has not set, but he perceives that it has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If the sun has not set, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If the sun has not set, and he perceives that it has not, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr " <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.22.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="529"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he gives a summary;"

msgstr "if he questions them;"

msgstr "if he recites when asked to do so;"

msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgstr "if he replies when asked a question;"

msgstr "if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;"

msgstr "if it is to a trainee nun;"

msgstr "if it is to a novice nun;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="530"></a>The second rule, the training rule on gone down, is finished."

